.TH CLIPX-CLEAR 1 "December 2024" "ClipX 0.2.0" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
clipx-clear \- clear clipboard history
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B clipx clear
.B \-\-all
.RI [ \-\-force ]
.br
.B clipx clear
.BI \-\-before " DATE"
.RI [ \-\-force ]
.SH DESCRIPTION
The
.B clipx clear
command removes entries from clipboard history. By default, it prompts
for confirmation before clearing.
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
.B \-\-all
Clear all clipboard history entries.
.TP
.BI \-\-before " DATE"
Clear entries created before the specified date.
Date format: YYYY-MM-DD
.TP
.B \-\-force
Skip confirmation prompt and clear immediately.
.SH EXAMPLES
.TP
Clear all history (with confirmation):
.nf
clipx clear --all
.fi
.TP
Clear all history (no confirmation):
.nf
clipx clear --all --force
.fi
.TP
Clear entries before a specific date:
.nf
clipx clear --before 2024-12-01
.fi
.TP
Clear old entries without confirmation:
.nf
clipx clear --before 2024-11-01 --force
.fi
.SH CONFIRMATION
Unless
.B \-\-force
is specified, the command will prompt:
.PP
.nf
Clear all clipboard history? (y/N):
.fi
.PP
Type 'y' or 'Y' to confirm, or any other key to cancel.
.SH EXIT STATUS
.TP
.B 0
Success (or cancelled by user)
.TP
.B 1
Failure (invalid arguments)
.SH SEE ALSO
.BR clipx (1),
.BR clipx-history (1)
